id: pm-ll50
title: Address pre-existing extension/SDK issues surfaced by PR #69 review (CodeRabbit)
description: "PR #69 was a pure barrel-split + error-surfacing change; CodeRabbit/Gemini reviewed the relocated code and surfaced PRE-EXISTING issues (all present on main before the split). PR #69 fixed the contained high-value ones (describeHandlerError non-Error objects; GitHub subpath path-traversal guard; reject ./.. managed dir names; bare Windows pm.cmd/pm.exe detection; missing health/validate schema props skipVectors/skipIntegrity/skipDrift/verboseDiagnostics). REMAINING (deferred to keep that PR focused; behavior-changing or contract-test-affecting): (1) src/cli/commands/extension/doctor.ts ~L147: package-vocabulary remediation commands generate 'pm package install'/'pm package adopt-all' but resolveAction() only accepts bare package targets for doctor/reload/catalog/init/explore/manage/list — remediation points users at erroring commands. (2) src/cli/commands/extension/install-sources.ts ~L194: cwd-relative npm specs like 'npm:packages/foo' fall through to npm pack as registry specs even when the dir exists locally; treat existing cwd-relative dirs as local. (3) src/cli/commands/extension/managed-state.ts ~L207: on schema/parse/read failure returns createEmptyManagedExtensionState() which install/manage/adopt then upsert+write, silently dropping all previously-managed entries after a transient read error; surface a hard failure or a non-persistable error state. (4) src/cli/commands/extension/scaffold.ts ~L189: writes scaffold files as it goes and only fails on first conflict, leaving partial package.json/extensions/ on EXIT_CODE.CONFLICT; do a read-only preflight conflict pass then write all-or-nothing. (5) src/sdk/cli-contracts/tool-option-contracts.ts L134: allowAuditUpdate sits in TOOL_CREATE_OPTION_CONTRACTS but the --allow-audit-update flag belongs to the update family; generated create schema accepts an unintended field and update schema rejects a valid one — move it to TOOL_UPDATE_OPTION_CONTRACTS and re-verify contract tests. Each needs regression tests."
type: Chore
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[5]: agent-ux,bug,code-quality,extensions,sdk
created_at: "2026-05-25T14:21:15.991Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-25T17:43:31.784Z"
author: claude-code-agent
parent: pm-rnpb
resolution: Implemented all remaining valid PR #69 reviewer threads with regression coverage.
expected_result: "Package remediation text, npm path resolution, managed-state safety, scaffold conflict handling, and update action schema contracts match the current CLI behavior."
actual_result: "Package doctor remediation uses flag-form commands, existing cwd-relative npm specs resolve as local packages, invalid managed state fails before mutation, scaffold conflicts are preflighted, and allowAuditUpdate is only in update-family schemas."
